  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Engineer | Tender",
  "description": "<p>On behalf of our client, who is an Original Equipment Maker (OEM), we are looking for a suitable candidate to join them as a <strong>Sales Engineer</strong>.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>To prepare tender quotations for new projects.</li><li>To respond to technical queries, supervise and check sales engineers' documents for tenders and quotations.</li><li>To pursue sales leads, conclude orders, and initiate the internal sales process and logistics.</li><li>To provide an update on sales activities and money collection status regularly.</li><li>To supervise Marketing Executive(s) and support their daily duties and responsibilities.</li><li>To check equipment condition highlighted by the Service Maintenance division via the feedback form and decide on the scope of work needed to carry out.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p><ul><li>Bachelor's degree in Electrical or Mechanical Engineering, or a related field. </li><li>Prior experience of at least 3 years in preparing tender quotations.</li><li>Proven skills in pursuing leads, closing sales, and initiating internal order processing and logistics coordination.</li><li>Strong presentation skills and able to articulate the expectations of customers.</li><li>A team player, able to work in a fast and dynamic environment.</li></ul></p><p><strong>Benefits</strong></p><ul><li>Permanent placement</li><li>Career progression</li><li>A reputable organisation in the evergreen industry</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Location: East</p><p>EA License: 22C0971 | EA Registration: R21101298<br /></p><p></p><p></p>",
